Write a function:

**promiseAll(promises)** that takes an array of promises and returns a new Promise.

- Resolves with an array of results (in original order) when ALL promises resolve
- Rejects with the first error encountered
- Empty array resolves immediately with `[]`
- Results must maintain order even if promises resolve out of order

```js
const result = await promiseAll([
  Promise.resolve(1),
  new Promise(r => setTimeout(() => r(2), 50)),
  Promise.resolve(3),
]);
// [1, 2, 3]  — in order, even though middle one resolved last

try {
  await promiseAll([
    Promise.resolve(1),
    Promise.reject(new Error('boom')),
    Promise.resolve(3),
  ]);
} catch (e) {
  // e.message === 'boom'
}
```

