exercises.instructions:
Build four classes for async task processing.

**Task(name, fn, priority):**
- `fn` is an async function. Properties: `status` ("pending"/"running"/"completed"/"failed"), `result`, `error`

**Queue():**
- `enqueue(task)` — inserts by priority (higher number = higher priority)
- `dequeue()` — removes and returns highest priority task
- `get size`
- `get isEmpty`

**Worker(name):**
- `async process(task)` — runs task.fn(), updates task status/result/error
- `get isIdle` — true when not processing
- `get tasksProcessed` — count

**Scheduler(concurrency):**
- `addTask(name, fn, priority)` — creates Task and enqueues
- `async start()` — processes all queued tasks using up to `concurrency` workers simultaneously
- `get stats` — returns `{ completed, failed, pending }`

```js
const scheduler = new Scheduler(2);
scheduler.addTask('fast', async () => 'done', 1);
scheduler.addTask('slow', async () => {
  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 50));
  return 'slow-done';
}, 2);
scheduler.addTask('fail', async () => { throw new Error('oops'); }, 1);

await scheduler.start();
scheduler.stats; // { completed: 2, failed: 1, pending: 0 }
```

exercises.solution:
class Task {
  constructor(name, fn, priority) {
    this.name = name;
    this.fn = fn;
    this.priority = priority;
    this.status = 'pending';
    this.result = null;
    this.error = null;
  }
}

class Queue {
  constructor() {
    this._items = [];
  }
  enqueue(task) {
    this._items.push(task);
    this._items.sort((a, b) => b.priority - a.priority);
  }
  dequeue() {
    return this._items.shift() || null;
  }
  get size() { return this._items.length; }
  get isEmpty() { return this._items.length === 0; }
}

class Worker {
  constructor(name) {
    this.name = name;
    this._idle = true;
    this._processed = 0;
  }
  async process(task) {
    this._idle = false;
    task.status = 'running';
    try {
      task.result = await task.fn();
      task.status = 'completed';
    } catch (err) {
      task.error = err;
      task.status = 'failed';
    }
    this._processed++;
    this._idle = true;
  }
  get isIdle() { return this._idle; }
  get tasksProcessed() { return this._processed; }
}

class Scheduler {
  constructor(concurrency) {
    this.concurrency = concurrency;
    this.queue = new Queue();
    this.workers = [];
    this.allTasks = [];
    for (let i = 0; i < concurrency; i++) {
      this.workers.push(new Worker('Worker-' + i));
    }
  }
  addTask(name, fn, priority) {
    const task = new Task(name, fn, priority);
    this.queue.enqueue(task);
    this.allTasks.push(task);
  }
  async start() {
    const running = [];
    while (!this.queue.isEmpty || running.length > 0) {
      while (running.length < this.concurrency && !this.queue.isEmpty) {
        const task = this.queue.dequeue();
        const worker = this.workers.find(w => w.isIdle);
        if (worker && task) {
          const p = worker.process(task).then(() => {
            running.splice(running.indexOf(p), 1);
          });
          running.push(p);
        }
      }
      if (running.length > 0) await Promise.race(running);
    }
  }
  get stats() {
    return {
      completed: this.allTasks.filter(t => t.status === 'completed').length,
      failed: this.allTasks.filter(t => t.status === 'failed').length,
      pending: this.allTasks.filter(t => t.status === 'pending').length,
    };
  }
}

