Write a function called `parseURL` that takes a URL string and returns an object with the following properties:
- `protocol`: the protocol (e.g., "https", "http", "ftp")
- `host`: the hostname (e.g., "example.com")
- `path`: the path portion (e.g., "/path/to/page"), or "" if none
- `query`: the query string without the "?" (e.g., "key=val&a=b"), or "" if none

Examples:
  parseURL("https://example.com/path?key=val")
  // { protocol: "https", host: "example.com", path: "/path", query: "key=val" }

  parseURL("http://google.com")
  // { protocol: "http", host: "google.com", path: "", query: "" }

  parseURL("ftp://files.server.com/docs")
  // { protocol: "ftp", host: "files.server.com", path: "/docs", query: "" }

exercises.starterCode:
