Write a function called `toggleHighlight` that takes:
- `elements`: an array-like list of DOM elements (each contains a number as text)
- `threshold`: a number

For each element, parse its textContent as a number. If the number is greater than or equal to the threshold, add the CSS class "highlight". Otherwise, remove it.

Examples:
  // Given: <span>10</span> <span>20</span> <span>30</span>
  toggleHighlight(spans, 20);
  // First span: no "highlight" class
  // Second span: has "highlight" class
  // Third span: has "highlight" class

exercises.solution:
function toggleHighlight(elements, threshold) {
  for (const el of elements) {
    const num = Number(el.textContent);
    if (num >= threshold) {
      el.classList.add('highlight');
    } else {
      el.classList.remove('highlight');
    }
  }
}

