exercises.instructions:
Write a function:

**asyncMap(array, asyncFn)**
- `array` is an array of values
- `asyncFn` is an async function `(item, index) => Promise`
- Calls `asyncFn` for every item concurrently (not sequentially)
- Returns a Promise that resolves with an array of results in the same order as the input
- If any call rejects, the returned promise rejects

```js
const results = await asyncMap([1, 2, 3], async (n) => n * 2);
// results === [2, 4, 6]

// All calls start at the same time (concurrent)
const times = await asyncMap([30, 10, 20], async (ms) => {
  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, ms));
  return ms;
});
// times === [30, 10, 20]  (order preserved)
```

exercises.starterCode:
async function asyncMap(array, asyncFn) {
  // your code here
}

exercises.solution:
async function asyncMap(array, asyncFn) {
  return Promise.all(array.map((item, index) => asyncFn(item, index)));
}

