exercises.instructions:
Write a function:

**asyncFilter(array, asyncPredicate)**
- `array` is an array of values
- `asyncPredicate` is an async function `(item) => Promise<boolean>`
- Tests each item concurrently using the predicate
- Returns a Promise that resolves with a new array containing only items where the predicate resolved to `true`
- Results maintain original order

```js
const result = await asyncFilter([1, 2, 3, 4, 5], async (n) => {
  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 10));
  return n % 2 === 0;
});
// result === [2, 4]
```

exercises.starterCode:
async function asyncFilter(array, asyncPredicate) {
  // your code here
}

exercises.solution:
async function asyncFilter(array, asyncPredicate) {
  const results = await Promise.all(
    array.map(async (item) => ({
      item,
      keep: await asyncPredicate(item),
    }))
  );
  return results.filter(r => r.keep).map(r => r.item);
}

