exercises.instructions:
Build a class:

**AsyncEventEmitter**
- `on(event, listener)` — registers an async listener for an event
- `off(event, listener)` — removes a specific listener
- `async emit(event, ...args)` — calls all listeners for the event with args, waits for all to complete, returns array of results
- `listenerCount(event)` — returns the number of listeners for an event

```js
const emitter = new AsyncEventEmitter();

emitter.on('save', async (data) => {
  await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 10));
  return `saved ${data}`;
});

const results = await emitter.emit('save', 'doc1');
// results === ['saved doc1']
```

exercises.starterCode:
class AsyncEventEmitter {
  constructor() {
    // your code here
  }

  on(event, listener) {}
  off(event, listener) {}
  async emit(event, ...args) {}
  listenerCount(event) {}
}

exercises.solution:
class AsyncEventEmitter {
  constructor() {
    this.listeners = {};
  }

  on(event, listener) {
    if (!this.listeners[event]) this.listeners[event] = [];
    this.listeners[event].push(listener);
  }

  off(event, listener) {
    if (!this.listeners[event]) return;
    this.listeners[event] = this.listeners[event].filter(l => l !== listener);
  }

  async emit(event, ...args) {
    if (!this.listeners[event]) return [];
    return Promise.all(this.listeners[event].map(l => l(...args)));
  }

  listenerCount(event) {
    return (this.listeners[event] || []).length;
  }
}

