exercises.instructions:
Build a class:

**Graph**
- `addVertex(vertex)` — adds a vertex (no duplicates)
- `addEdge(v1, v2)` — adds an undirected edge between v1 and v2
- `removeEdge(v1, v2)` — removes the edge between v1 and v2
- `removeVertex(vertex)` — removes vertex and all its edges
- `getNeighbors(vertex)` — returns array of adjacent vertices
- `hasEdge(v1, v2)` — returns boolean
- `bfs(start)` — breadth-first traversal, returns array of visited vertices in order
- `get size` — number of vertices

```js
const g = new Graph();
g.addVertex('A');
g.addVertex('B');
g.addVertex('C');
g.addEdge('A', 'B');
g.addEdge('B', 'C');
g.bfs('A'); // ['A', 'B', 'C']
```

