- `fetchPage(page)` is an async function that returns `{ data: [...], hasMore: boolean }`
- Returns an async iterable (works with `for await...of`)
- Each iteration yields individual items from the current page
- Automatically fetches the next page when the current one is exhausted
- Stops when `hasMore` is `false`

Implement using `Symbol.asyncIterator` or an async generator.

```js
const fetcher = createPaginatedFetcher(async (page) => {
  const items = page <= 3 ? [page * 10 + 1, page * 10 + 2] : [];
  return { data: items, hasMore: page < 3 };
});

const all = [];
for await (const item of fetcher) {
  all.push(item);
}
// all === [11, 12, 21, 22, 31, 32]
```

