exercises.instructions:
Write a function `makeDiamond(letter)` that returns a diamond string for the given letter.

The diamond starts with 'A' at the top and bottom, and widens to the given letter in the middle.

```js
makeDiamond("C")
// =>  "  A  \n B B \n" +
//     "C   C\n" +
//     " B B \n  A  \n"
```

Each line should have the same width (2*n - 1 where n = letter position).

exercises.starterCode:
function makeDiamond(letter) {
  // your code here
}

exercises.solution:
function makeDiamond(letter) {
  const idx = letter.charCodeAt(0) - 65;
  const width = 2 * idx + 1;
  const lines = [];
  for (let i = 0; i <= idx; i++) {
    const ch = String.fromCharCode(65 + i);
    let line;
    if (i === 0) {
      line = " ".repeat(idx) + ch + " ".repeat(idx);
    } else {
      line = " ".repeat(idx - i) + ch + " ".repeat(2 * i - 1) + ch + " ".repeat(idx - i);
    }
    lines.push(line);
  }
  const full = [...lines, ...lines.slice(0, -1).reverse()];
  return full.join("\n") + "\n";
}

